@rdblue : One example of custom transform usage is to define a custom target column name for an existing transform function. For instance - 
```scala
// gives us `timestamp_day` as target col
PartitionSpec.builderFor(schema)
    .day("timestamp") 

 // gives us `_ADBE_DAY` as target col
PartitionSpec.builderFor(schema)
    .add(1 /* fieldId */, "_ADBE_DAY", "day")
```

